northern summer), which accounts\nfor the high-altitude tropical dust maxima unveiled by Mars Climate Sounder.\nDust-driven deep convection have strong implications for the Martian dust\ncycle, thermal structure, atmospheric dynamics, cloud microphysics, chemistry,\nand robotic and human exploration.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Aug 2012 18:26:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Nov 2012 11:48:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Dec 2012 08:21:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-05-21"}
